      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Partial set of postcard size reproductions of original photographic prints from the Rijksbureau voor Kunsthistorische Documentatie, the Netherlands Institute for Art History in the Hague. "The photographs illustrate an iconographic index of Dutch and Flemish paintings, drawings, and prints, form the late Medieval to Renasissance periods that protry biblical, mythological, allegorical, and historical scenes. . . .Originally devised by H. van de Waal, professor of art history at the University of Leiden and completed by a group of scholars after his death."---(quoted from Fogg Library, Harvard University catalog record). This aide is a summary list of sections with corresoponding box numbers. For more detailed content description, refer to Decimal index of the art of the Low Countries; D.I.A.L.; abridged ed. of the ICONCLASS system. (1971) Art and Architecture Z697.A8.N47 1971 (oversize).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_arr1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged alphabetically by the alphanumeric divisions of the ICONCLASS classification system.</p>  
      </arrangement>
